results.name: Nike Dunk Low PRM Halloween (2021) (TD)
results.story: The Nike Dunk Low Premium TD ‘Halloween’ celebrates October 31 with a seasonally appropriate colorway of the retro hoops shoe, complete with a translucent rubber outsole that glows in the dark. The leather upper combines an off-white base with contrasting black overlays covered in tonal graphics that depict balefully staring eyes. Starfish orange accents make their way to the signature Swoosh, tongue and sockliner, featuring a spider graphic alongside traditional Nike branding.

results.name: Nike Dunk Low Social Status Free Lunch Strawberry Milk (TD)
results.story: Crafted in partnership with the influential sneaker boutique, the Social Status x Nike Dunk Low TD ‘Strawberry Milk’ draws inspiration from public school systems’ free lunch programs. Varying shades of pink are applied to the upper, featuring a soft nubuck base with plush velvet construction on the eyestay, collar and forefoot overlay. Unique details include braided rope laces, a TPU gel Swoosh and Tyvek tongue tags. The pastel hues up top are contrasted by a vintage off-white midsole, reinforced by an olive green rubber outsole.

results.name: Nike Dunk Low Social Status Free Lunch Chocolate Milk (TD)
results.story: The Social Status x Nike Dunk Low TD ‘Chocolate Milk’ is taken from the retailer’s ‘Free Lunch’ collection, inspired by federally assisted meal programs in public schools. The sneaker features an eclectic build, highlighted by brown leather overlays and plush yellow velour on the toe box and quarter panel. A white mini-Swoosh is embroidered on the lateral forefoot, complementing a larger TPU gel Swoosh in pink. A green Tyvek tongue tag displays mismatched Nike and Social Status branding, while the shoe’s ‘ingredients’ are printed on the medial heel. Underfoot, a bright blue rubber outsole provides grippy traction.

results.name: Nike Dunk Low Bright Crimson Game Royal (TD)
Nike Dunk Low Sail Multi-Camo (TD)
results.story: The Nike Dunk Low SE TD ‘Sail Multi-Camo’ enlivens the vintage hoops shoe with military-inspired prints in clashing colors. The mismatched camo patterns — ranging from a neutral greyscale design to traditional woodland hues — are interspersed throughout the leather eyestay, heel tab and forefoot and heel overlays. The rest of the upper is crafted from off-white textile with a dark green leather Swoosh. Additional branding elements include a woven Nike tongue tag and heel tabs that display an embroidered Nike wordmark on the left shoe and a basketball graphic on the right.

results.name: Nike Air Force 1 Low Hare Space Jam (TD)
results.story: Releasing as part of a sprawling collection centered around ‘Space Jam: A New Legacy,’ the Nike Air Force 1 ‘06 TD ‘Hare’ places the spotlight on two of the film’s leporine protagonists. The scaled-down low-top is rendered in classic two-tone color blocking, featuring a white leather upper with vibrant accents in Light Blue Fury. On the right shoe, Bugs Bunny’s likeness appears on the woven tongue tag and a large patch affixed to the lateral quarter panel. Lola Bunny’s presence is registered in the same areas of the left shoe.

results.name: Nike Lebron 18 Low Wile E. vs Roadrunner Space Jam (TD)
results.story: The Nike LeBron 18 Low TD ‘Wile E. x Roadrunner’ features asymmetrical color blocking in a nod to a pair of combative nemeses from ‘Space Jam: A New Legacy.’ The right shoe is dedicated to Roadrunner, who appears on the sockliner and whose distinctive plumage is represented by the blue textile upper. The left shoe gestures at Wile E. Coyote with a beige textile upper and a red Swoosh marked with Acme Co. branding. The character's likeness is similarly depicted on the sockliner. Both shoes feature a durable rubber cupsole and Tune Squad badging on the adjustable ankle strap.

results.name: Nike Air Force 1 Low Computer Chip Space Jam (TD)
results.story: Celebrating the release of LeBron James’ ‘Space Jam: A New Legacy,’ the Air Force 1 '07 TD ‘Computer Chip’ gives this scaled-down silhouette a technical look, highlighted by subtle electronic-circuit graphics throughout the black leather upper. A closer look reveals that some of the lines form the shapes of instantly recognizable members of the Tune Squad, including Bugs Bunny and new recruit LeBron James. A woven Nike tongue tag delivers a vibrant burst of Light Blue Fury atop the tongue. Underfoot, a milky translucent outsole provides traction.

results.name: Nike Lebron 18 Low Summit White Space Jam (TD)
results.story: Launching as part of a larger collection celebrating the release of ‘Space Jam: A New Legacy,’ the Nike LeBron 18 Low TD ‘Lola Bunny’ spotlights one of LeBron James’ feisty Tune Squad teammates. This scaled-down version of LBJ’s signature low-top carries a color-blocked textile upper secured with elastic no-tie laces and an adjustable ankle strap. The latter is decorated with a Tune Squad logo, while mismatched sockliners display the cartoon likeness of LeBron James and Lola Bunny. A translucent teal rubber outsole provides durable traction underfoot.

results.name: Nike Dunk Low UNC (2021) (TD)
results.story: The Nike Dunk Low TD ‘University Blue’ treats the iconic silhouette to classic color blocking that recalls the original ‘Be True to Your School’ series from 1985. No-tie elastic laces secure the leather upper, featuring a crisp white base with contrasting overlays in a pastel blue finish. Step-in comfort is provided by a padded mesh collar and breathable nylon tongue, topped with a woven Nike tag for an OG touch. Underfoot, the rubber outsole features a concentric-circle traction pattern for reliable grip.

results.name: Nike Dunk Low UNDEFEATED Canteen Dunk vs. AF1 Pack (TD)
results.story: Releasing as part of the ‘Dunk vs. AF-1’ pack, the Undefeated x Nike Dunk Low SP TD ‘Canteen’ showcases a familiar design inspired by the ‘Inside Out Priority’ Air Force 1 collaboration from 2006. Varying shades of brown are applied to the leather upper, featuring a tonal shemagh print throughout the quarter panel and forefoot. A leather Swoosh in Lemon Frost delivers a vibrant pop of contrasting color, while Undefeated’s Five Strikes logo decorates the lateral heel and woven tongue tag.

results.name: Nike Dunk High Game Royal (TD)
Nike Dunk Low Light Bone Tropical Twist (TD)
results.story: The Nike Dunk Low TD ‘Tiffany’ delivers a miniaturized version of the retro hoops shoe made for little feet. No-tie elastic laces secure the leather upper, featuring a neutral Light Bone base with contrasting black overlays and a signature Swoosh in Tropical Twist. Reminiscent of the ‘Tiffany’ Dunk Low SB from 2005, the pastel hue makes repeat appearances on Nike branding hits atop the heel tab and woven tongue tag. Underfoot, the outsole features the same grippy traction pattern found on the shoe’s mainline counterpart.

results.name: Nike Air Griffey Max 1 Varsity Royal (TD) (2021)
results.story: The 2021 edition of the Nike Air Griffey Max 1 TD ‘Varsity Royal’ brings back a scaled-down version of Ken Griffey Jr.’s signature shoe on the occasion of its 25th anniversary. Inspired by the Seattle Mariners’ vintage ‘80s uniforms, the trainer features a nubuck and leather upper in blue and white. The Kid’s jersey number adorns the adjustable ankle strap, which works in tandem with elastic no-tie laces for a secure fit. The midsole packs a Volt-colored Air sole unit under the heel for lightweight cushioning.

results.name: Nike Air Force 1 Low LE Triple White (TD)
Nike Air Max 1 CLOT Kiss of Death (2021) (TD)
Nike Dunk Low SP Orange Pearl (TD)
results.story: The Nike Dunk Low TD ‘Orange Pearl’ outfits a scaled-down version of the iconic silhouette in a leather upper with classic two-tone color blocking. An off-white base is contrasted by a subtle pastel finish on the Swoosh, heel tab and forefoot and heel overlays. A soft nylon mesh tongue combines with a padded textile collar to deliver a comfortable fit for little feet. Underfoot, the rubber outsole features the same grippy tread used on the OG ‘80s high-top.

results.name: Nike Dunk Low Retro White Black (TD)
results.story: The Nike Dunk Low TD ‘Black White’ offers a scaled-down version of the retro hoops shoe for little feet, rendered in an elemental two-tone color scheme that spans both the leather upper and tooling. Design details remain faithful to Peter Moore’s original 1985 silhouette, highlighted by a woven Nike tag atop a lightly padded nylon tongue. The rubber outsole, featuring a traction pattern the Dunk shares with the Air Jordan 1, offers superior grip.

results.colorway: Black / Black / Platinum Tint / Glacier Ice

results.name: Nike Dunk Low UNLV (TD)
results.story: The Nike Dunk Low TD ‘UNLV’ revives one of the original colorways of the brand’s iconic ‘Be True to Your School’ series from 1985. Rendered in low-top form and miniaturized for little feet, the classic silhouette features a two-tone leather upper in Medium Grey and Varsity Red. A padded collar provides a comfortable fit around the ankle, while elastic no-tie laces deliver easy on and off. The red rubber outsole features the same distinctive traction pattern of the original.
